abstract: Analysis published in the Cochrane Database of Systematic Reviews finds supplemental calcium does not prevent preterm birth or improve bone density in pregnant women.
snippet: Supplemental calcium does not prevent preterm birth or improve bone density in pregnant women, according to a new report.
lead_paragraph: Supplemental calcium does not prevent preterm birth or improve bone density in pregnant women, according to a new report.

headline.main: Childbirth: Limited Gains From Supplemental Calcium
headline.print_headline: Childbirth: Limited Gains From Supplemental Calcium
headline.seo: Pregnant Women’s Gains From Extra Calcium May Be Limited
